snippet.title: Amber   New
snippet.description:
I care about you so fucking much

Lyrics:
When it felt like everything was happening
It felt like you're the one to guide me
Came in an unexpected manner
Always there when I needed a friend
Someone unexpected I've always found comfort in

First to know with the gender struggles
Identity is something I never understood
But with you by my side
My hand in your hand our fingers interlocked
Lend me your ear every time I need to talk

You helped me test this shit out
You helped me cry this shit out
You helped me figure out how I'm wired
You helped me figure out all my ticks
It's like my mental state will never be the same
But suddenly I'm honestly cool with it

Looked to others when I sought comfort in you
Never fair until I heard those words from you
Never in a million years I thought
But I guess you liked me too
Now I'm exploring a whole new avenue

Gotta figure out my passion
But my passion is you
Don't know what to do
I Just wanna put a smile up on your face
Give you a little taste of happiness
Don't know why you wanted me
Not sure why you still do
But I won't let this opportunity go to waste
So I'll work it out and I'll take the cake
Be the best boyfriend ever made
Even if I Get a taste of fame
Don't want to restart again
Not cause I'm afraid of hearbreak
Not cause I'm sick of the talking phase
But if it isn't you then I'm done...
Gotta win this game
Like in basketball or that hockey game
I will remain
Your number once choice I mean after all
You saw me fucked up
You saw me thru my worst
You saw my mistakes
You still said I had worth
Now I gotta work hard to prove it
Don't ever wanna be worthless
You're worth the work I gotta put it in
